        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 3 at 2:00PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles north of Three Rivers, or 28 miles northeast
of Visalia, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Pinehurst, Potwisha Campground, Park Ridge, Azalea
Campground, Ash Mountain Sequoia Park HQ, Buckeye Flat Campground,
Shadequarter Mtn, Grant Grove, Crystal Springs Campground, Dorst
Creek Campground, Sunset Campground, Grant Grove Visitor Center,
Giant Forest, and Yokuts Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
